name: PFNN: From environment to economy: what to expect from new German government
description:

BERLIN (AP) — Germany's new government will need to find a compromise between environmentalists concerned about climate change and economic liberals determined not to stifle growth.
The coalition of Chancellor Angela Merkel's conservatives and the left-leaning Social Democrats led by Martin Schulz was sworn in Monday.
Merkel, 62, was seeking the fourth term as chancellor and her fourth government. Schulz, 60, was hoping to become Germany.
